{"title_page": "The Sandman (audio drama)", "text_new": "{{Short description|Audio drama based on the television series Doctor Who}}\n{{Infobox Big Finish|\n|title=The Sandman\n|publisher=[[Big Finish Productions]]\n|series=[[Doctor Who]]\n|number=37\n|featuring=[[Sixth Doctor]]<br/>[[Evelyn Smythe]]\n|cover= Sandman (Doctor Who).jpg\n|writer=[[Simon A. Forward]]\n|director=[[Gary Russell]]\n|producer=Gary Russell and<br>[[Jason Haigh-Ellery]]\n|executive_producer=[[Jacqueline Rayner]]\n|production_code=7CF\n|set_between=''[[Project Twilight|Project: Twilight]]'' and<br>''[[Jubilee (Doctor Who audio)|Jubilee]]''\n|length=1 hr 56 mins\n|date=24 October 2002\n|}}\n'''''The Sandman''''' is a [[Big Finish Productions]] [[List of Doctor Who audio plays by Big Finish|audio drama]] based on the long-running British [[science fiction on television|science fiction television]] series ''[[Doctor Who]].\n\n==Plot==\nWhen the Sixth Doctor and Evelyn visit the Clutch \u2014 a large community of spacecraft that never settle on one planet \u2014 Evelyn discovers that the Doctor is held in fear by the Galyari. They know him as \"the Sandman\", a figure from their mythology, an ancient [[bogeyman]] \u2014 and the Doctor does not deny being that which they regard with fear.\n\n==Cast==\n*The [[Doctor (Doctor Who)|Doctor]] \u2014 [[Colin Baker]]\n*[[Evelyn Smythe]] \u2014 [[Maggie Stables]]\n*Director Nrosha \u2014 [[Anneke Wills]]\n*Orchestrator Shol \u2014 [[Mark Donovan]]\n*Commander Brel \u2014 Mark Wharton\n*[[The Bone of Contention|Mordecan]] \u2014 [[Robin Bowerman]]\n*Nintaru \u2014 Stephanie Colburn\n*General Voshkar \u2014 [[Ian Hogg (actor)|Ian Hogg]]\n\n==Notes==\n*Anneke Wills played the [[First Doctor|First]] and [[Second Doctor]]'s companion [[Polly (Doctor Who)|Polly]] from 1966 to 1967.\n*The Galyari come up against the [[Seventh Doctor]] in [[Dreamtime (Doctor Who audio)|Dreamtime]].\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bigfinish.com/37-Doctor-Who-The-Sandman Big Finish Productions \u2013 ''The Sandman'']\n\n{{Sixth Doctor audios}}\n{{Sandman navbox}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sandman, The}}\n[[Category:2002 audio plays]]\n[[Category:Sixth Doctor audio plays]]\n\n\n{{DoctorWho-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Audio drama based on the television series Doctor Who}}\n{{Infobox Big Finish|\n|title=The Sandman\n|publisher=[[Big Finish Productions]]\n|series=[[Doctor Who]]\n|number=37\n|featuring=[[Sixth Doctor]]<br/>[[Evelyn Smythe]]\n|cover= Sandman (Doctor Who).jpg\n|writer=[[Simon A. Forward]]\n|director=[[Gary Russell]]\n|producer=Gary Russell and<br>[[Jason Haigh-Ellery]]\n|executive_producer=[[Jacqueline Rayner]]\n|production_code=7CF\n|set_between=''[[Project Twilight|Project: Twilight]]'' and<br>''[[Jubilee (Doctor Who audio)|Jubilee]]''\n|length=1 hr 56 mins\n|date=24 October 2002\n|}}\n'''''The Sandman''''' is a [[Big Finish Productions]] [[List of Doctor Who audio plays by Big Finish|audio drama]] based on the long-running British [[science fiction on television|science fiction television]] series ''[[Doctor Who]].\n\n==Plot==\nWhen the Sixth Doctor and Evelyn visit the Clutch \u2014 a large community of spacecraft that never settle on one planet \u2014 Evelyn discovers that the Doctor is held in fear by the Galyari. They know him as \"the Sandman\", a figure from their mythology, an ancient [[bogeyman]] \u2014 and the Doctor does not deny being that which they regard with fear.\n\n==Cast==\n*The [[Doctor (Doctor Who)|Doctor]] \u2014 [[Colin Baker]]\n*[[Evelyn Smythe]] \u2014 [[Maggie Stables]]\n*Director Nrosha \u2014 [[Anneke Wills]]\n*Orchestrator Shol \u2014 [[Mark Donovan]]\n*Commander Brel \u2014 Mark Wharton\n*[[The Bone of Contention|Mordecan]] \u2014 [[Robin Bowerman]]\n*Nintaru \u2014 Stephanie Colburn\n*General Voshkar \u2014 [[Ian Hogg (actor)|Ian Hogg]]\n\n==Notes==\n*Anneke Wills played the [[First Doctor|First]] and [[Second Doctor]]'s companion [[Polly (Doctor Who)|Polly]] from 1966 to 1967.\n*The Galyari come up against the [[Seventh Doctor]] in [[Dreamtime (Doctor Who audio)|Dreamtime]].\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bigfinish.com/37-Doctor-Who-The-Sandman Big Finish Productions \u2013 ''The Sandman'']\n\n{{Sixth Doctor audios}}\n{{Sandman navbox}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sandman, The}}\n[[Category:2002 audio plays]]\n[[Category:Sixth Doctor audio plays]]\n\n\n{{DoctorWho-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:Update date format tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Sandman_(audio_drama)"}
